projects.name: Olympic Medal Insights: Data Analysis and Visualization
projects.description: Conducted in-depth analysis of Olympic medal tallies, country performance trends, and top athlete achievements using Python, leveraging libraries like Pandas and NumPy for data manipulation. Developed an interactive data visualization app using Streamlit, allowing users to explore insights on medal dominance, country-specific performance by sport, and standout athletes. Provided actionable insights into Olympic trends, enhancing understanding of global athletic performance through data-driven exploration and visualization.

projects.name: Movie Recommendation System
projects.description: Developed a sentiment analysis model for IMDB movie reviews using Multinomial Naive Bayes and Stochastic Gradient Descent, accurately classifying user sentiments. Leveraged machine learning techniques to analyze large datasets and identify patterns in movie reviews, enabling data-driven recommendations of top-rated movies. Enhanced the recommendation system by integrating sentiment analysis, improving the relevance and accuracy of movie suggestions for users.

projects.name: Fuel Efficiency Prediction
projects.description: Developed a fuel efficiency prediction model using TensorFlow, leveraging features such as engine distance traveled and the number of car cylinders for accurate forecasting. Applied deep learning techniques to analyze complex relationships between multiple features, improving the precision of fuel efficiency predictions. Utilized TensorFlow API to build and optimize the model, enhancing its performance and reliability for real-world automotive applications.
